  "local_port": 47956,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are good watches for men under $200?",
  "response": "Finding a quality men's watch under $200 is entirely possible, as there are numerous brands and styles that offer great functionality, durability, and aesthetics without breaking the bank. Below is a curated list of some of the best options available in various categories to suit different tastes and needs:\n\n### 1. **Casio G-Shock Series**\n- **Price Range:** ~$100-$200\n- **Features:** Shock resistance, water resistance (often up to 200m), multiple alarms, stopwatches, backlighting.\n- **Why Choose It:** Renowned for their durability and rugged design, G-Shock watches are perfect for those with an active lifestyle or who prefer a sporty look.\n\n### 2. **Seiko 5 Automatic**\n- **Price Range:** ~$100-$200\n- **Features:** Automatic movement, day/date display, water resistance (commonly 30m).\n- **Why Choose It:** Offers the elegance of an automatic watch without the high price tag. Seiko 5 is a classic choice for both casual and formal settings.\n\n### 3. **Timex Weekender**\n- **Price Range:** ~$30-$50\n- **Features:** Indiglo backlight, interchangeable straps, water resistance (up to 30m).\n- **Why Choose It:** Affordable, versatile, and stylish with a wide variety of color options and strap materials, making it easy to match different outfits.\n\n### 4. **Citizen Eco-Drive Chandler**\n- **Price Range:** ~$150-$200\n- **Features:** Solar-powered (Eco-Drive), date display, water resistance (100m).\n- **Why Choose It:** Eco-friendly with low maintenance since it never needs a battery change. Stylish design suitable for everyday wear.\n\n### 5. **Orient Bambino**\n- **Price Range:** ~$150-$200\n- **Features:** Automatic movement, domed crystal, various dial colors and textures, water resistance (30m).\n- **Why Choose It:** Known for its classic and elegant design, the Orient Bambino is a favorite among those seeking a dress watch with a refined look.\n\n### 6. **Hamilton Khaki Field Quartz**\n- **Price Range:** ~$200 (often found on sale below this price)\n- **Features:** Quartz movement, military-inspired design, water resistance (100m).\n- **Why Choose It:** Combines Swiss craftsmanship with a timeless field watch aesthetic, suitable for both casual and semi-formal occasions.\n\n### 7. **Tissot Everytime**\n- **Price Range:** Around $200 (occasionally slightly above)\n- **Features:** Swiss quartz movement, minimalist design, water resistance (30m).\n- **Why Choose It:** Offers Swiss precision and a sleek, minimalist style that's versatile for various outfits and settings.\n\n### 8. **MVMT Classic Series**\n- **Price Range:** ~$100-$150\n- **Features:** Quartz movement, minimalist design, interchangeable straps, water resistance (50m).\n- **Why Choose It:** Stylish and modern designs appealing to fashion-forward individuals. Often lightweight and comfortable for everyday wear.\n\n### 9. **Bulova Classic**\n- **Price Range:** ~$150-$200\n- **Features:** Quartz or automatic movement options, stainless steel case, various dial styles, water resistance (30m-50m).\n- **Why Choose It:** Combines traditional aesthetics with reliable performance, offering a range of designs from dressy to more casual styles.\n\n### 10. **Invicta Pro Diver**\n- **Price Range:** ~$100-$180\n- **Features:** Automatic or quartz movement, water resistance (200m), unidirectional bezel, luminous hands.\n- **Why Choose It:** Provides a classic dive watch look with robust features, suitable for both water activities and everyday use.\n\n### **Things to Consider When Choosing a Watch:**\n\n1. **Movement Type:**\n   - **Quartz:** Battery-powered, accurate, and low maintenance.\n   - **Automatic/Magnetic:** Powered by the motion of your wrist, no battery needed but may require regular servicing.\n\n2. **Style:**\n   - **Dress Watches:** Sleek and minimalist, suitable for formal occasions.\n   - **Sport Watches:** Durable and feature-rich, ideal for active lifestyles.\n   - **Casual Watches:** Versatile designs that can be worn daily.\n\n3. **Features:**\n   - **Water Resistance:** Ensure it meets your needs, especially if you plan on swimming or diving.\n   - **Additional Functions:** Such as chronographs, alarms, date displays, or GPS.\n\n4. **Material:**\n   - **Case and Bracelet:** Stainless steel is durable and hypoallergenic, while leather straps offer a classic look.\n   - **Crystal:** Sapphire crystal is more scratch-resistant but typically more expensive, while mineral glass is more common in affordable watches.\n\n5. **Brand Reputation:**\n   - Research brands known for their quality and customer service to ensure you're getting good value for your money.\n\n### **Where to Buy:**\n\n- **Authorized Retailers:** Ensure warranty and authenticity.\n- **Official Brand Websites:** Often have the latest models and exclusive deals.\n- **Reputable Online Retailers:** Such as Amazon, Jomashop, or Macy\u2019s, but verify seller credibility.\n- **Local Watch Stores:** Provide personalized service and the ability to try on watches before purchasing.\n\n### **Final Tips:**\n\n- **Set a Budget:** Even within the under $200 range, prices vary. Determine what features are most important to you.\n- **Read Reviews:** Look for customer feedback on reliability and longevity.\n- **Consider Your Lifestyle:** Choose a watch that complements your daily activities and wardrobe.\n\nWith careful consideration of these factors, you can find a stylish, reliable, and affordable watch that suits your personal taste and needs without exceeding your budget.",
